ENTRY       EC 4.1.2.45                 Enzyme
NAME        trans-o-hydroxybenzylidenepyruvate hydratase-aldolase;
            2'-hydroxybenzalpyruvate aldolase;
            NsaE;
            tHBPA hydratase-aldolase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-carbon lyases;
            Aldehyde-lyases
SYSNAME     (3E)-4-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate hydro-lyase
REACTION    (3E)-4-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate + H2O = salicylaldehyde + pyruvate [RN:R05136]
ALL_REAC    R05136
SUBSTRATE   (3E)-4-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate [CPD:C06203];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     salicylaldehyde [CPD:C06202];
            pyruvate [CPD:C00022]
COMMENT     This enzyme is involved in naphthalene degradation. The enzyme catalyses a retro-aldol reaction in vitro, and it accepts a broad range of aldehydes and 4-substituted 2-oxobut-3-enoates as substrates [4].
